com.jnape.palatable.lambda.functions

Interface Fn0<A>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - the result type
    All Superinterfaces:
    Applicative<A,Fn1<Unit,?>>, Contravariant<Unit,Profunctor<?,A,Fn1>>, Fn1<Unit,A>, Function<Unit,A>, Functor<A,Fn1<Unit,?>>, Monad<A,Fn1<Unit,?>>, Profunctor<Unit,A,Fn1>, Supplier<A>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface Fn0<A>
extends Fn1<Unit,A>, Supplier<A>
    A function taking "no arguments", implemented as an Fn1<Unit, A>.
    See Also:
    Fn1, Supplier
